"title": "6645: eternal life, nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6645: eternal life, nature of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Triumph over death and infinitely extended life. It also means a unique quality of life, knowing God in this life and sharing the life of Christ. Its source is God himself.</p>\n<h2>Eternal life is knowing God and enjoying his eternal blessings</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:3\">JHN 17:3</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps16:11\">PSA 16:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps21:4-Ps21:6\">PSA 21:4–21:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:3-Eph1:14\">EPH 1:3–1:14</a></p>\n<h3>Eternal glory is the believer's inheritance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:17\">2CO 4:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:3\">DAN 12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:10\">2TI 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:4\">1PE 5:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:10\">1PE 5:10</a></p>\n<h3>Contrasted with eternal judgment and rejection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:46\">MAT 25:46</a></strong> <em>Interpreters differ over whether “eternal punishment” implies an experience that continues for ever, or annihilation which is eternal in the sense of being irreversible.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:2\">DAN 12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:46\">MAT 25:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:16\">JHN 3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:8-2Thess1:9\">2TH 1:8–1:9</a></p>\n<h3>The work of helping others come to eternal life</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:35-John4:36\">JHN 4:35–4:36</a></p>\n<h2>Eternal life as endless life</h2>\n<h3>The guarantee of the resurrection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:20-1Cor15:22\">1CO 15:20–15:22</a></strong> <em>“firstfruits” because the resurrection of Jesus Christ is seen as the beginning of a harvest.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:15\">PSA 49:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:19\">ISA 26:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:14\">1TH 4:14</a></p>\n<h3>Death will be vanquished</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:4\">REV 21:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:8\">ISA 25:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:26\">1CO 15:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:50-1Cor15:57\">1CO 15:50–15:57</a></p>\n<h3>Believers will live for ever</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:25-John11:26\">JHN 11:25–11:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:34-Luke20:36\">LUK 20:34–20:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:51\">JHN 6:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:54\">JHN 6:54</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:58\">JHN 6:58</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:51\">JHN 8:51</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:17\">1JN 2:17</a></p>\n<h2>Eternal life as a quality of life</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:10\">JHN 10:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:14\">JHN 4:14</a></p>\n<h3>One of the blessings associated with the kingdom of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:29\">MAT 19:29</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:30\">MRK 10:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:30\">LUK 18:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:18\">LUK 18:18</a></p>\n<h3>Life with Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:67-John6:69\">JHN 6:67–6:69</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:5\">JHN 15:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:4\">COL 3:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:10\">1TH 5:10</a></p>\n<h2>Eternal life as experiencing Jesus Christ's life</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:20\">GAL 2:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:10-2Cor4:11\">2CO 4:10–4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:4\">ROM 6:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:8\">ROM 6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:10-Rom8:11\">ROM 8:10–8:11</a></p>\n<h2>God is the source and giver of eternal life</h2>\n<h3>God the Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:3\">JHN 17:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:26\">DEU 5:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps36:9\">PSA 36:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:2\">PSA 42:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps56:13\">PSA 56:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:32\">MAT 22:32</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:27\">MRK 12:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:38\">LUK 20:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:13\">1TI 6:13</a></p>\n<h3>God the Son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:6\">JHN 14:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:4\">JHN 1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:25-John11:26\">JHN 11:25–11:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:3\">JHN 17:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:1-1John1:2\">1JN 1:1–1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:20\">1JN 5:20</a></p>\n<h3>God the Holy Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:63\">JHN 6:63</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:6\">2CO 3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:8\">GAL 6:8</a></p>",
